  "Getting Started": "",
  "media loading": "",
  "Welcome to reactgg, the interactive way to master Modern React.": "",
  "When we started making this course, our goal was ambitious – make it the best programming course ever created. Over a year and a half later, we couldn't be happier with how it turned out.": "",
  "Before we dive in, here are some things to help you get the most out of the course.": "",
  "First, despite the dopamine rush you got when you gave us money, you haven't actually accomplished anything yet. I beg of you –&nbsp;don't let this course collect dust with all those Udemy courses you've purchased over the years.": "",
  "Second, learning new things is hard. We've tried our best to make this course as simple and as enjoyable as possible –&nbsp;but at the end of the day, you're going to have to sit down and put in the work. It'll be hard, but if you do, and you're able to get through the course, I promise you you'll know more React than most senior React developers.": "",
  "Third, is how we think about education. A lot of Twitter heads will preach complexity and sell you their course as the cure. That's not our thing. We're more interested in helping you establish a first-principles mental model for how to think in React than we are teaching you how to glue a bunch of npm packages together.": "",
  "You can see that in how we've structured the course. Each time you're introduced to a new topic, you're given some text and a video about that topic. From there, once you've gone through both (and we recommend you start with the text first and then watch the video as a review), you're given a quiz as a gentle test of your understanding.": "",
  "If you find the quiz to be difficult, go back through the text and video one more time. The entire course is linear, meaning each section builds on top of the next. If you move on before feeling comfortable, it'll just get worse.": "",
  "Finally, the most important part, before you move onto the next section you'll be given a collection of challenges optimized for scenarios you'd see in real life. If you're able to get through all of these, you can feel confident that you're able to move on. And if at any point you get stuck and aren't sure what to do next, create a new thread and we'll be there to help.": "",
  "As is, the course is about 60% done with the remaining sections coming out over the next few months. So you don't have to keep checking in, we'll send you email updates when new sections go live.": "",
  "This course wasn't cheap, and the opportunity cost of your time going through it is even more expensive. We don't take that for granted and we hope it lives up to the bar we've set for ourselves.": "",
  "Good luck.": "",
